===Etymology===
[[Image:ClemensXI.jpg|thumb|right|A coin.]]
From Old French ''[[coigne]]'' "wedge, cornerstone, die for stamping," from Latin ''[[cuneus]]'' "wedge." English [[quoin]] means "cornerstone."

